<subSubSection id="A31A9B7E47A52E6043AEFDA2E85577D8" pageId="14" pageNumber="37" type="comments">
<paragraph id="B6809072DB44D4CA65E40823C3F4DB5A" pageId="14" pageNumber="37">Comments.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3774FE2A1F4E00816CA947E445ED4B25" pageId="14" pageNumber="37">
Although not reported in 
<bibRefCitation id="EC0BDCB9E02B25E93EC8DA083B8FF3DC" author="Aiken, SG" journalOrPublisher="NRC Research Press, National Research Council of Canada, Ottawa" pageId="35" pageNumber="58" publicationUrl="http://nature.ca/en/research-collections/research-projects/flora-canadian-arctic-archipelago/" refId="B1" refString="Aiken, SG, Dallwitz, MJ, Consaul, LL, McJannet, CL, Boles, RL, Argus, GW, Gillett, JM, Scott, PJ, Elven, R, LeBlanc, MC, Gillespie, LJ, Brysting, AK, Solstad, H, Harris, JG, 2007. Flora of the Canadian Arctic Archipelago: Descriptions, Illustrations, Identification, and Information Retrieval [CD-ROM]. NRC Research Press, National Research Council of Canada, Ottawa, http://nature.ca/en/research-collections/research-projects/flora-canadian-arctic-archipelago/" title="Flora of the Canadian Arctic Archipelago: Descriptions, Illustrations, Identification, and Information Retrieval [CD-ROM]" url="http://nature.ca/en/research-collections/research-projects/flora-canadian-arctic-archipelago/" year="2007">Aiken et al. (2007)</bibRefCitation>
for the CAA, this species was first reported for the CAA from Banks Island by 
<bibRefCitation id="937D5AB07DBF7EEEF8997C0AD7B4C2F3" author="Mason, WRM" journalOrPublisher="Canadian Field-Naturalist" pageId="39" pageNumber="62" pagination="363 - 367" refId="B66" refString="Mason, WRM, Shewell, GE, Cody, WJ, 1972. A plant collection from the southern interior of Banks Island, N.W.T. Canadian Field-Naturalist 86: 363 - 367" title="A plant collection from the southern interior of Banks Island, N. W. T." volume="86" year="1972">Mason et al. (1972</bibRefCitation>
, as 
<taxonomicName id="3D2F0FB58ED663E12C108A17D09944AC" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Elymus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Elymus innovatus" order="Poales" pageId="14" pageNumber="37" phylum="Spermatophyta" rank="species" species="innovatus">
<emphasis id="831F19899B1FBE9E01C546470D766A4E" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="37">Elymus innovatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Beal), based on a collection from the Masik River Valley (
<geoCoordinate id="94F9EA3D41BA3F4C7DB8C8B8936001C0" degrees="71" direction="north" minutes="37" orientation="latitude" precision="925" value="71.61667">71°37'N</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate id="469E7F14195BA5388B30AD041D7EFCFA" degrees="123" direction="west" minutes="6" orientation="longitude" precision="925" value="-123.1">123°6'W</geoCoordinate>
, 20 July 1968, 
<emphasis id="106436CF103E380C8F73B18E539FD5E2" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="37">W.R.M. Mason 93</emphasis>
, DAO-543555, not seen). There is also a collection in CAN (two sheets) from Sachs Harbour (Banks Island, Northwest Territories), previously determined as 
<taxonomicName id="37480B36EAAB1DBB4CC5681E357093D9" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Agropyron" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Agropyron violaceum" order="Poales" pageId="14" pageNumber="37" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="species" species="violaceum">
<emphasis id="78CC81D7A8716E22FF85B0FC2D027232" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="37">Agropyron violaceum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Hornem.) Lange (det. A.E. Porsild) and 
<taxonomicName id="C300953FD5385FDDBE95630604C240EE" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Elymus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Elymus alaskanus subsp. latiglumis" order="Poales" pageId="14" pageNumber="37" phylum="Spermatophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="alaskanus" subSpecies="latiglumis">Elymus alaskanus subsp. latiglumis</taxonomicName>
(Scribn. &amp; J.G. Smith) 
<normalizedToken id="AFE921FBE941FD675F590D5F34116329" originalValue="Á">A</normalizedToken>
. 
<normalizedToken id="855FAB8F819E8EBDE903BDA8FB2D0E6E" originalValue="Löve">Loeve</normalizedToken>
(det. M.E. Barkworth, 1993), that has been re-determined as this species (det. J.M. Saarela). The taxon was mapped on southern Banks Island by 
<bibRefCitation id="816B3F1D9D570CBF477570193DF5C3FB" author="Porsild, AE" journalOrPublisher="National Museum of Natural Sciences, National Museums of Canada, Ottawa" pageId="40" pageNumber="63" pagination="1 - 667" refId="B76" refString="Porsild, AE, Cody, WJ, 1980. Vascular Plants of the Continental Northwest Territories, Canada. National Museum of Natural Sciences, National Museums of Canada, Ottawa: 1 - 667" title="Vascular Plants of the Continental Northwest Territories, Canada" year="1980">Porsild and Cody (1980)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="6EDCF78BB3C463F8FCA00E2EC4F15E7C" author="Barkworth, ME" editor="Barkworth, ME" journalOrPublisher="Oxford University Press, Oxford and New York" pageId="36" pageNumber="59" pagination="353 - 369" refId="B9" refString="Barkworth, ME, 2007. Leymus Hochst. In: Barkworth, ME, Capels, KM, Long, S, Anderton, LK, Piep, MB, Eds., Flora of North America North of Mexico, Volume 24 Magnoliophyta: Commelinidae (in part): Poaceae, part 1. Oxford University Press, Oxford and New York: 353 - 369" title="Leymus Hochst." volumeTitle="Flora of North America North of Mexico, Volume 24 Magnoliophyta: Commelinidae (in part): Poaceae, part 1." year="2007">Barkworth (2007)</bibRefCitation>
, probably based on the Mason collection and/or one or more correctly-determined duplicates of the Sachs Harbour collection in other herbaria. It grows in Alaska, the Yukon Territory, and the western Northwest Territories (
<bibRefCitation id="0AA8ED84BEA5B8FCBA5CCCC5BC3490FB" author="Barkworth, ME" editor="Barkworth, ME" journalOrPublisher="Oxford University Press, Oxford and New York" pageId="36" pageNumber="59" pagination="353 - 369" refId="B9" refString="Barkworth, ME, 2007. Leymus Hochst. In: Barkworth, ME, Capels, KM, Long, S, Anderton, LK, Piep, MB, Eds., Flora of North America North of Mexico, Volume 24 Magnoliophyta: Commelinidae (in part): Poaceae, part 1. Oxford University Press, Oxford and New York: 353 - 369" title="Leymus Hochst." volumeTitle="Flora of North America North of Mexico, Volume 24 Magnoliophyta: Commelinidae (in part): Poaceae, part 1." year="2007">Barkworth 2007</bibRefCitation>
) with Sachs Harbour and the Masik River Valley the only known locations in the CAA. 
<taxonomicName id="1EB77B540358B3CD391E4F9D24488A10" authorityName="Pilg" authorityYear="1947" baseAuthorityName="Beal" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Leymus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Leymus innovatus" order="Poales" pageId="14" pageNumber="37" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="innovatus">
<emphasis id="667C1F547A1DE1A70A036C06ED375B47" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="37">Leymus innovatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Beal) Pilg. and 
<taxonomicName id="BF10ECB5B71A5877995F3EE6E31A26A6" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Leymus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Leymus mollis" order="Poales" pageId="14" pageNumber="37" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mollis">
<emphasis id="14BD6C11F72D1D777B572EAF588EEB7E" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="37">Leymus mollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-the only two species of the genus in the CAA-may be distinguished by the following key (adapted from 
<bibRefCitation id="5A9AB7F2F409B11D8384823413C0548B" author="Barkworth, ME" editor="Barkworth, ME" journalOrPublisher="Oxford University Press, Oxford and New York" pageId="36" pageNumber="59" pagination="353 - 369" refId="B9" refString="Barkworth, ME, 2007. Leymus Hochst. In: Barkworth, ME, Capels, KM, Long, S, Anderton, LK, Piep, MB, Eds., Flora of North America North of Mexico, Volume 24 Magnoliophyta: Commelinidae (in part): Poaceae, part 1. Oxford University Press, Oxford and New York: 353 - 369" title="Leymus Hochst." volumeTitle="Flora of North America North of Mexico, Volume 24 Magnoliophyta: Commelinidae (in part): Poaceae, part 1." year="2007">Barkworth 2007</bibRefCitation>
):
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0FAD1AA658FD35DD3F330701812D4239" pageId="14" pageNumber="37">
<table id="FFC24E31FB5A9B63EAFDCF4694479851" inLine="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="37">
